This paper focuses on improving the performance of the Apriori algorithm on the MapReduce framework, which is commonly used for large-scale data processing. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the database (cs.DB), distributed computing (cs.DC), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes optimizations for computation cost reduction, which could fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) or information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
